'''Iain Lowson''' was the author of [[1998]]'s "[[Down & Out on DB-24]]" in the UK-published [[Polyhedron (UK)|''Polyhedron'']] [[Polyhedron (UK) 2|2]]&ndash;[[Polyhedron (UK) 3|3]] and an author of the ''[[The Official Star Wars Fact File]]'', published [[2002]] through [[2005]]. Before this, he worked on [[Titan Magazines|Titan's]] [[Star Wars: The Official Magazine|Official Star Wars Magazine]], as well as the original version of the UK Star Wars Fan Club. He was co-creator, editor and sole writer on the discontinued [[De Agostini]] follow-up to the Fact File, based on the Star Wars Miniatures game from [[Wizards of the Coast]]. That project, with floor plans from artist Andy J. Hepworth, was well received by fans in the few places it saw release, but never made it past issue four.

Iain later worked on the UK version of De Agostini's ''[[Star Wars: The Official Starships & Vehicles Collection]]''.

